    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Scope creep is a common issue in software development, and it's great that you're addressing it. One technique to help manage scope creep is to use the \"MoSCoW\" method, which categorizes stakeholder requests into Must-Haves, Should-Haves, Could-Haves, and Won't-Haves. This helps prioritize and focus on the most critical requirements. You can also consider implementing a \"Stop Doing\" list to identify and eliminate non-essential features that are causing scope creep.",
      "source": "target",
